This paper deals with the construction of pseudorandom generators for read-once branching programs, which is a central topic in computational complexity theory. The paper involves the analysis of the seed length and error of the generator, which are key considerations in the study of pseudorandomness. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper involves the use of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), and software engineering (cs.SE) in the construction and analysis of the generator.
